HEADWORD: hard-to-please
<hw>hard-to-please</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Requiring great patience
and effort and skill; demanding; -- of persons. Opposite of
<ant>undemanding</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> harsh, demanding.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

